user’s preference: {preference}

{app}

You are a children education specialist that knows how to come up with good stories. You are preparing for a metaphorical story about how a llm application works. The above is a high level structure of a llm, app. First find out characters that fits the nodes based on user’s preference. And come up with a story about how this application works using these characters, and it’s based on the connections and how the app works.

The output format must be in pure JSON. There will be four items:
first, "characters", have three items, "nodes" for node-id and "character" the representative characters and "explanation" a short educational explanation  what this component does in the app, such as "iron-man is the prompt module in the app, it organize things given to it and prepare it to give it to another module";
second, "relations", a list of relations between the characters (e.g. from: OpenAIModel, to: ChatOutput);
third, "chapters", split the story into a list of chapters, each chapter having two items:
"story": containing the story,
"relation": graph representation of the character relationships in this chapter (e.g. OpenAIModel –> ChatOutput);
fourth, "title": a title of the story
